items.title: PVV Infra to build 1 GW TOPCon plant in Andhra Pradesh
items.summary:
- PVV Infra signed a **₹650 crore** MoU with the Andhra Pradesh Economic Development Board to set up a **1 GW TOPCon solar cell manufacturing facility** in Visakhapatnam.
- The 30-acre site near the airport project is expected to create about 350 direct jobs and over 450 indirect jobs, per the press release.
- The project supports India’s renewable infrastructure goals and aims to boost domestic solar cell production in Andhra Pradesh.

items.title: Musashi India expands Bengaluru plant for EV components
items.summary:
- Musashi India completed the second phase of its Bengaluru plant expansion, aiming for full operation by *December 2025*.
- The upgrade adds forging, machining and heat‑treatment to support 100–750cc bikes, 100–125cc scooters and *e-axles*, lifting annual scooter/motorcycle transmissions to *6.5 million* sets.
- The facility spans 32,000 sq m, with rooftop solar (2.16 million kWh) and over *96% green energy*, reinforcing its commitment to a sustainable *EV supply chain*.

items.title: Goods exports down 11.8% in October, trade deficit widens on gold imports
RITES, AP to sign MoU for infra and industrial development
items.author: ET Infra Desk
items.summary:
- *RITES* signs a MoU with the *APEDB* to provide consultancy for *infrastructure* and *industrial development* in the state.
- The pact covers *feasibility studies*, *DPRs*, *project management consultancy*, *bid management* and *third-party inspection* across transport, ports, waterways, power, water and wastewater, buildings and industrial infra.
- *RITES* aims to facilitate investments and support *planning* and *execution* of projects across key sectors in Andhra Pradesh.

items.title: Pricol to invest up to ₹600 crore as it enters fresh capex cycle
Nuvoco Vistas to acquire Algebra Endeavour for ₹200 crore
items.author: ETManufacturing Desk
items.summary:
- *Nuvoco Vistas Corporation* signed a Securities Purchase Agreement to acquire 100% of Algebra Endeavour Private, the holding company of *Vadraj Energy*, to bolster captive power for cement operations.  
- The deal involves a cash consideration of up to ₹200 crore, including ₹191.63 crore to *JSW Cement* and ₹8.36 crore to *Alpha Alternatives*, with the closing subject to regulatory approvals.  
- Upon completion, Algebra will become a wholly owned subsidiary of Nuvoco and a related party under SEBI regulations.

items.title: Apple sales growth in India at 6-year low of 18%
Stellantis sets ₹10,000 crore India component export goal for 2026
items.author: Alenjith K Johny, ET Bureau
items.summary:
- Stellantis aims to export about **₹10,000 crore** in India‑sourced components by 2026 via its suppliers, up from about ₹4,000 crore today.
- The Hosur plant exports **95%** of its output, with capacity for **300,000 engines** and **374,000 gearboxes**.
- India is the third‑largest auto market with **4.2 million** sales in 2024, accounting for ~**2%** of Stellantis’ global volume, with **₹11,000 crore** invested in India across three plants.

Vaishnaw: Design capabilities to guide ECMS approvals
items.summary:
- Vaishnaw urged firms to build local *design capabilities* and make them a criterion for **ECMS** approvals.
- He called building design teams a *non-negotiable* part of the electronics manufacturing journey.
- The ECMS expansion aims to boost investments, create jobs, and stress *quality*, *self-reliance*, and the vision of *Viksit Bharat*.

Flying Wedge Defence signs MoU with Andhra Pradesh govt for autonomous combat aircraft facility
Zetwerk wins ECMS nod for optical transceivers & PCBs
items.author: ETManufacturing Desk
items.summary:
- *ECMS approval* enables Zetwerk to locally produce optical transceivers and multi-layer PCBs.
- Zetwerk's subsidiaries, *Zetfab India* (complex PCBs) and *Zetchem Supply Chain Services* (optical transceivers including *SFP* units), will boost domestic manufacturing and curb imports.
- Industry and government leaders emphasized a goal of a *$500B electronics ecosystem*, strengthening *self-reliance* through local components.

items.title: TPREL commissions 300 MW DCR solar for NHPC in Rajasthan
items.author: ETEnergyWorld Desk
items.summary:
- Tata Power Renewable Energy commissioned a **300 MW DCR‑compliant** solar project for **NHPC** at Karnisar Bhatiyan, Bikaner, Rajasthan.
- The project is part of NHPC's 450 MW solar capacity and supplies power to *Punjab State Power Corporation* under a PPA.
- It employed 300+ local workers, uses TP Solar modules from Tirunelveli, and boosts **TPREL** renewables capacity to 11.6 GW (5.8 GW operational: 4.7 GW solar; 1.1 GW wind).

items.title: Schaeffler India steps up crackdown on counterfeit bearings; thousands of fake products seized in Delhi raids
items.summary:
- **Schaeffler India** intensified its crackdown on counterfeit bearings, seizing thousands of fake **FAG wheel bearings**, ball bearings, and packaging in coordinated Delhi raids.
- The raids, conducted with police support across five locations, underscored risks to equipment safety and customer trust from counterfeit parts.
- Customers and partners are urged to verify authenticity via the **Schaeffler OriginCheck** app, looking for two‑dimensional barcodes and laser-marked product details.

items.title: India unveils ARKA GKT-1 intelligent-power chip
items.author: ETManufacturing Desk
items.summary:
- **ARKA GKT-1** is India’s first-generation intelligent-power platform-on-a-chip for edge AI, smart energy and industrial systems.
- It fuses *multi-core computing*, analogue sensing, memory and power management into a single system-on-chip to serve smart utilities, metering, battery management and automation.
- The launch, unveiled by Union IT Minister Ashwini Vaishnaw, highlights domestic semiconductor progress and reinforces India’s path to self-reliance and a local silicon value chain.

items.title: GOCL completes sale of IDL Explosives to Apollo Defence Industries
items.summary:
- *GOCL* completes the sale of *IDL Explosives* Ltd to **Apollo Defence Industries**, marking the Hinduja Group’s exit from the explosives and detonators segment.
- The transfer of IDL’s manufacturing units to **Apollo Defence Industries** paves the way for expansion in the defence sector, while GOCL monetises assets including Hyderabad land.
- Post-divestment, *GOCL* plans to evolve into an energy company in line with its long-term growth aspirations.

items.title: KEC secures ₹1,016 cr orders across businesses
items.summary:
- KEC International, part of the RPG Group, won orders worth **₹1,016 crore**, including its first oil-and-gas order in the Middle East.
- The **transmission and distribution** division secured orders for towers, hardware and poles in the Middle East and Americas, and 400 kV lines in the UAE.
- Year-to-date orders surpassed **₹17,000 crore**, signaling growth and GCC expansion, with cables and conductors also winning domestic and overseas projects.

items.title: Enlight Metals strengthens auto supply chain with OEMs
items.author: ETAuto Desk
items.summary: - *Enlight Metals* has entered strategic OEM partnerships with Toyota, Volkswagen, Hyundai and Mahindra to strengthen India’s auto supply chain.\n- It connects OEMs with verified suppliers via a **digital sourcing** platform, boosting transparency, pricing and quality.\n- The company plans to expand digital sourcing and logistics with **predictive procurement tools**, sustainability tracking and data-driven supply-chain management.

items.title: Uno Minda gets approval under ECMS for camera module assembly
items.author: ETAuto Desk
items.summary: - Uno Minda has received approval under MeitY's *Electronic Components Manufacturing Scheme* (**ECMS**) for its *Camera Module Assembly* business, enabling deeper domestic value addition.\n- The approval was handed to CEO Vivek Jindal by Ministers *Ashwini Vaishnaw* and *Jitin Prasada*, signaling stronger domestic electronics collaboration.\n- The ECMS program aims to boost component-level manufacturing, strengthen supply chains, and support MSMEs and emerging manufacturers to enhance India's global competitiveness.

items.title: Centre clears ₹7,172 cr ECMS projects
items.author: ETManufacturing Desk
items.summary:
- The Centre approved 17 projects worth **₹7,172 crore** under the **Electronics Component Manufacturing Scheme (ECMS)**, spanning nine states and targeting about **₹65,111 crore** in cumulative production.
- Selected firms include Jabil Circuit India, Aequs Consumer Products, Uno Minda, ASUX Safety Components India, Zetfab India, TE Connectivity India, and Meena Electrotech.
- Long-term success will hinge on strengthening *design capabilities*, ensuring **six-sigma quality** across products, and partnering with domestic suppliers, with a new skilling framework and enhanced supply-chain resilience.

items.title: Texmaco bags DMRC ballastless-track contract
items.author: ET Infra Desk
items.summary: - Texmaco Rail has won a **₹15.06 crore** DMRC contract to install, test, and commission **ballastless track systems** along with buffer stops across select *Delhi Metro corridors*.\n- The scope covers **5.8 track-km** across Saket-G (Line-11), Sarita Vihar Depot (Line-10), and Noida Electronic City (Line-3), starting **1 December 2025** and finishing in **12 months**.\n- This project aligns with *Make in India* and *Aatmanirbhar Bharat*, as Texmaco continues a larger DMRC program (22 of 58 T-KM completed) and expands high-precision rail solutions.

items.title: Army, IAF to induct 16 indigenous anti-drone systems
items.author: ANI
items.summary:
- The *Army* and *IAF* will order 16 indigenous anti-drone systems with a **2-km laser strike range**.
- The DRDO's Mark 2 system uses a **10 Kilowatt laser**, doubling the engagement distance.
- India has demonstrated high-energy laser capabilities, including a **30-kW DEW** and CHESS tests.

items.title: India-Chile CEPA talks in December
items.summary:
- The next round of talks between India and Chile on a proposed **CEPA** is expected in **December**, an official said.
- CEPA aims to widen the 2006 PTA to cover **digital services**, **investment promotion**, MSMEs, and access to **critical minerals** India seeks under the pact.
- In 2024-25, bilateral trade remained modest: exports to Chile were about **$1.15B** (down 2.46%), imports about **$2.60B** (up 72%), with auto and pharma as top exports and minerals as top imports; Chile is a key partner in the Latin American region.

items.title: Kings Infra signs ₹2,500-cr aquaculture park deal
items.author: PTI
items.summary:
- Kings Infra Ventures Ltd signs a ₹2,500-cr aquaculture park deal with Andhra Pradesh to build an **AI-driven** facility near Srikakulam.
- The 500-acre park will train 5,000 professionals and enable multi-species farming powered by the **BlueTechOS** AI system.
- The project aims to position Andhra Pradesh as a hub for *sustainable seafood production*, unlocking new economic opportunities and investment.

items.title: Jakson Group launches ₹8,000-cr solar project in MP
items.summary:
- *Phase 1* will establish 3 GW cell and 4 GW module capacity as part of a planned 6 GW solar manufacturing hub in Maksi, Madhya Pradesh.
- Phase 1 is expected to generate about 1,700 jobs, with the overall plan creating up to ~4,000 jobs and boosting MP's manufacturing profile.
- The project aligns with India’s *clean energy transition* and *Aatmanirbhar Bharat* goals, positioning MP as a manufacturing and logistics hub.

items.title: Tata AutoComp wins third Deming Prize in two years
items.summary:
- Tata AutoComp Systems wins the Deming Prize for the third time in two years in *Total Quality Management* (TQM), awarded to Tata AutoComp Hendrickson Suspensions (THSL).
- Arvind Goel says three prizes in two years underscore the importance of *Total Quality Management* and highlight back-to-back wins with a focus on *customer-centric transformation*.
- The 2024 prize went to the company’s Composites Division and Tata Ficosa, making THSL the world's first commercial vehicle suspension system maker to receive the award.

items.title: H2 going to be important for volume & value sales for Allied Blenders & Distillers: Managing Director
Samsung, Hyundai announce domestic investments after US-South Korea trade deal
India's coal imports rise 14% in September
items.author: PTI
items.summary:
- *September* coal imports rose *13.54%* to *22.05 MT*, driven by festive-season demand.
- *Non-coking coal* imports at *13.90 MT* (vs *13.24 MT* in Sept 2024) and *coking coal* at *4.50 MT* (vs *3.39 MT* a year ago).
- For Apr-Sep 2025, *non-coking coal imports* fell to *86.06 MT* while *coking coal imports* rose to *31.54 MT*, per mjunction.

Indian states changing rules of biz game, initiate slew of reforms encouraging startups, manufacturing
SK to invest 128 trillion won in Korea through 2028
items.author: IANS
items.summary:
- SK Group will invest 128 trillion won ($87.9B) through 2028 in Korea, prioritizing *chip manufacturing* to meet growing *AI* demand.
- It plans four large-scale fabs at the Yongin chip cluster and the 860B-won Trinity Fab, with potential Yongin spending rising to 600 trillion won and an open ecosystem.
- The plan includes phased construction, sustained domestic hiring of 8,000+ jobs yearly and a 14,000–20,000 annual job boost, plus an *AWS*-backed AI data center in Ulsan for 2027.

Venezuela seeks to expand critical minerals partnership with India
items.author: ETEnergyWorld Desk
items.summary:
- Venezuela seeks to broaden economic engagement with India beyond oil, prioritizing *critical minerals* and *mining*. 
- The talks revived the *India–Venezuela Joint Committee Mechanism*, with mentions of ONGC's operations, *pharma trade*, and opportunities in the *auto sector*. 
- Separately, an MoU in Andhra Pradesh aims to digitise logistics via the *Unified Logistics Interface Platform (ULIP)*, signaling broader bilateral cooperation.

items.title: VinGroup explores EV, battery and clean energy investments in Telangana
items.author: ETAuto Desk
items.summary:
- VinGroup expressed interest in setting up **EV manufacturing**, **battery storage**, and other clean-energy ventures in Telangana.
- The talks touched on opportunities across **EVs**, **renewable energy** (solar and wind) and the state’s proposed **Bharath Future City**, with an invitation to attend the Telangana Rising Global Summit 2025.
- Officials called the discussions a step toward expanding Telangana's global investment partnerships and promoting *green* and *innovation-led development*.

items.title: India aims to double aerospace manufacturing market by 2030
items.author: Siva G, TIMESOFINDIA.COM
items.summary:
- The *aerospace components market* is **$2B** now, targeting **$4B** by 2030 with growing opportunities to manufacture aircraft components.
- The aviation sector is set to be the world’s third-largest market, with airports rising from 74 (2014) to 164 today and domestic passengers up from ~1.8 lakh/day to ~4.6 lakh.
- Initiatives include **hub-and-spoke** airport development, categorizing airports as *mega/medium/small*, and sustaining 10–12% annual growth while expanding capacity.

items.title: India's homoeopathic sector rapidly becoming global hub for high-quality medicines, say experts
Amber to acquire majority stake in Shogini Technoarts
items.summary:
- **Amber Group** will acquire a majority stake in **Shogini Technoarts**, expanding its capabilities in *PCB manufacturing* through backward integration. 
- The deal will broaden Amber's product offerings, enable faster scaling, and reduce reliance on external suppliers by bringing more operations in-house. 
- The transaction value has not been disclosed; Shogini reported Rs 390.74 crore turnover in the financial year ended March 2025.
